<form class="form-horizontal">
	<div class="form-group" id="publications">
		<div class="col-md-12">
			<h4>Filters</h4>
			<p>You may use the following fields to filter the displayed
				graph:</p>
			<dl>
				<dt>Year</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>Displays publications of the selected years. You might
						select a maximum of five "years" or let it empty to search for
						publications from all years.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Type</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>
						Displays publications of the selected type. DBLP classifies
						publications using the following types: Journal Article,
						Conference and Workshop Papers, Parts in Books or Collections,
						Editorship, Reference Works and Informal and Other Publications.
						You can find more information about publications classification <a
							target="_blank"
							href="http://dblp.uni-trier.de/faq/What+types+does+dblp+use+for+publication+entries.html">here</a>.
					</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Venue</dt>
				<dd>Displays publications that are from the selected venue,
					e.g., CSCW - Conference on Computer Supported Cooperative Work,
					IEEE, CCIS - Communications in Computer and Information Science,
					books & theses, reference works, edited collections, and so on.</dd>
			</dl>
			<p>
				<i>Obs: Those filters only dispose information that exists into
					the displayed graph. </i>
			</p>
			<br>
			<h4>Graph</h4>
			<p>You are free to manipulate the graph with some different
				interactions:</p>
			<dl>
				<dt>Mouse wheel</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>Zoom in/out.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Single click node</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>Highlight the node and its respective edges.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Hover</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>If you hover your mouse over a publication node, it'll show
						a tooltip with the publication title.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Double click publication node</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>Displays a pop-up window with some informations about the
						respective publication like: Title, Year, Type, Venue and Path.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Double click coauthor node</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>You'll be redirected to the graph page of the respective
						coauthor.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Click and drag node</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>You can click and drag the node to move it to other points
						in the screen.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Click and drag screen</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>You can click and drag the screen background to move it
						without changing the nodes position.</p>
				</dd>
			</dl>
		</div>
	</div>
</form>